<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/129.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Minister</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the board of engineers
                            to be composed of Colonel William L. Sibert as chief and Mr. Arthur P.
                            Davis and Professor D. W. Mead to proceed to China to make a
                            supplementary examination of the Hwai River region, I am authorized by
                            my instructions to say that the Government of the Republic of China
                            desires the board to come to China at as early a date as possible.</p>
                        <p>I have already had the pleasure of informing my Government by cable of
                            the designation of Colonel Sibert as chief of the board.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kai Fu Shah</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>